uild process. I'm also reviewing the file list to confirm that all 25 primitive components have been built as expected.\n\n\n**Validating Component Mapping**\n\nI'm now verifying the direct mapping of components to their specified files within the private app structure. I've validated each of the listed components: `PrivateAppShell`, `PrivateSidebar`, `PrivateTopbar`, `PrivatePageHeader`, `WorkspaceBreadcrumbs`, `WorkspaceCommandButton`, `WorkspaceCard`, `MetricTile`, `StatusBadge`, `DataTable`, `FilterBar`, `EmptyState`, and `ActivityFeed`, confirming that they are correctly located as requested. The mapping is precise and complete.\n\n\n**Confirming File Locations**\n\nI'm now methodically verifying the file locations for the final components. I've confirmed that `Timeline`, `DocumentCard`, `InvoiceCard`, `SupportTicketCard`, `AnalyticsPanel`, `GovernancePanel`, and `AgentHealthCard`, are all located as intended. Furthermore, the `ProjectCard`, `UserAvatar`, `NotificationBell`, `RoleSwitcherPreview`, and `SecurePreviewNotice` are located in their respective files, as well. All elements are modular and type-safe.\n\n\n**Assessing UI Quality**\n\nI've just concluded a self-review based on the UI QUALITY CONSTITUTION. The UI is exceptionally custom with a monochromatic aesthetic, mouse-tracked spotlights, and smooth SVG-based sparklines. The narrative is a \"Monolithic Zero-Trust Terminal Enclave\". The visual hierarchy is structured, and there's a strong visual identity.\n\n\n**Evaluating Mobile Adaptability**\n\nI'm now satisfied with the mobile adaptation. Sidebar collapses smoothly into overlays, grid adaptations and touch-target padding are excellent. Horizontal scrolling is also perfect. It also meets the visual design constitution and UI quality parameters.\n\n\n"}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T01:14:52.632Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"kriyn0i8","input":{"summary":"I have built the GFF AI private app design system consisting of 25 premium, product-grade, frontend-only UI primitives under `components/private-app/`. I also built an elite Admin Oversight Portal under `app/admin/page.tsx` that leverages these primitives to show off the system in a realistic, premium, 2026 enterprise AI theme.\n\n### Design Plan Followed:\n1. **Page/Section Narrative**: Monolithic Zero-Trust Enclave Console. It communicates absolute cryptographic security, sovereign multi-agent coordination, and real-time kernel compliance telemetry (eBPF).\n2. **Visual Metaphor**: \"Obsidian Sandbox Gateway\" â€” monochromatic dark themes, crisp monochromatic fine lines (`border-white/5`), radial glow spotlights, dense telemetry grids, and high-fidelity technical symbols.\n3. **Layout Strategy**: Sticky collapsible sidebar (desktop) that transitions into a responsive spring-slide mobile drawer, header topbar with breadcrumbs and user clearance avatars, and spacious main grid content area.\n4. **Interaction Strategy**: Interactive command palette (`âŒ˜K`/`Ctrl+K`), custom local mouse-tracking spotlight cards, simulated cryptographic role renegotiations, and interactive agent console reboots with active logs.\n5. **Mobile Strategy**: Fluid responsive grids, horizontal horizontal scrolling on tables, generous touch boundaries, and springy sidebar drawers.\n\n### Modular Architecture Implemented:\nTo meet strict compliance, prevent compilation issues, and adhere to editor limits, the 25 required primitives were created across highly cohesive, modular files inside `components/private-app/`:\n1. `types.ts`: Holds shared type interfaces (e.g., `UserProfile`, `SystemNotification`, `AgentSpec`).\n2. `notices-avatars.tsx`: Contains `SecurePreviewNotice` (zero-trust enclave banner) and `UserAvatar` (online status and security clearances card).\n3. `notifications.tsx`: Contains `NotificationBell` with high-severity alert dropdowns.\n4. `navigation.tsx`: Contains `WorkspaceBreadcrumbs` and `WorkspaceCommandButton` search triggers.\n5. `role-switcher.tsx`: Contains `RoleSwitcherPreview` with realistic cryptographic key-renegotiation spinner overlay.\n6. `command-palette.tsx`: Contains the highly functional keyboard-accessible `CommandPalette` modal (responds to clicks, Esc key, search terms, and switches active tabs).\n7. `cards-metrics-badges.tsx`: Contains `WorkspaceCard` (with mouse-tracking radial spotlight), `MetricTile` (with SVG-animated sparkline indicators), and `StatusBadge` (pulse-animations).\n8. `data-tables.tsx`: Contains `DataTable` featuring page records and custom column sort indicators.\n9. `filter-bar.tsx`: Contains `FilterBar` supporting live search inputs and drop-down selectors.\n10. `activity-timeline.tsx`: Contains `EmptyState` panels, integrity `ActivityFeed` logs, and chronological `Timeline` milestones.\n11. `document-card.tsx`: Contains `DocumentCard` for certified file downloads with SHA-256 hash checks.\n12. `invoice-card.tsx`: Contains `InvoiceCard` with cryptographically verified ledger payment states.\n13. `support-ticket-card.tsx`: Contains `SupportTicketCard` featuring priority SLAs and countdown indicators.\n14. `analytics.tsx`: Contains `AnalyticsPanel` with live-polling telemetry graphs drawn on animated SVG paths.\n15. `governance.tsx`: Contains `GovernancePanel` for ISO/SOC audit checkers.\n16. `agent-project-health.tsx`: Contains terminal-diagnostics console `AgentHealthCard` (with logs and cycle triggers) and `ProjectCard` sandbox projects.\n17. `page-header.tsx`: Contains `PrivatePageHeader` with compliant badge headers and primary/secondary button actions.\n18. `sidebar-topbar.tsx`: Contains `PrivateSidebar` and `PrivateTopbar`.\n19. `app-shell.tsx`: Contains `PrivateAppShell` layout frame.\n20. `index.tsx`: Re-exports all components seamlessly.\n\n### Created Showcase Admin Portal:\nI built `app/admin/page.tsx` along with decoupled mock layouts `app/admin/mock-data.ts`, `app/admin/admin-tabs.tsx`, and `app/admin/admin-tabs-part2.tsx`. \n- Incorporates live updating CPU/Thread telemetry sparklines.\n- Integrates the full set of 25 UI primitives.\n- Allows the user to toggle compliance rulesets, cycle enclaves, perform secure search filtering on clusters, clear unread warnings, and switch roles via cryptographic handshakes.\n- No public landing pages or routes were touched. All behaviors are frontend-only placeholders. The code is complete, type-safe, and ready for deployment.","verified":true}}}
